Court grants the State's motion to vacate the Deferred Judgment Agreement and enters conviction on count 1 burglary.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Forty-five (45) days jail, imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/job search or combination;
5) Have no contact with Michael Gadzinski and Gianni Smith;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Continue with current mental health treatment; 
8) Submit DNA sample and pay costs;
9) Pay costs of action; 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Minutes.

On count 1, burglary, the Court approves the Deferred Judgment Agreement for a period of thirty (30) months.
Review date:  07-27-2017
On counts 2 and 3, disorderly conduct and criminal trespass to dwelling, the Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend twenty-one (21) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 2 only, commencing on 07-01-15 at 6:00 p.m.;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) No contact with Courtney Livingood, Michael Gadzinski and Gianni Smith;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
5) Defendant is to continue with this mental health treatment currently involved in;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) maintain absolute sobriety;
9) spend thirty-nine (39) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 2 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
The Court orders that all copies of records from Libertas Treatment Center be sealed.  
$250.00 cash bail is applied to court costs in this matter.
